19/11/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The Seventh Cetinje Parliamentary Forum began in Podgorica on Monday (November 19th), with officials from Serbia, Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Greece, Italy, Macedonia and Montenegro participating.
They are exchanging views about how memberships in the Partnership for Peace programme and NATO are factors for regional stability.
The situation in the region, foreign policy challenges, education and culture, and economic issues will be among the topics of discussion.
(Antena M - 19/11/07;
Mina - 18/11/07)
